news.title: Orissa HC seeks clarity on flat registration restrictions
news.para: The Orissa high court on Wednesday directed the Inspector General of Registration (IGR) to notify a clarification on applicability of restrictions imposed on registration of apartments.

news.title: SWAMIH Investment Fund-I raises over Rs 15,000 crore at its final close
news.para: Irfan A. Kazi, chief investment officer, SWAMIH Investment Fund, said, "The fund has already achieved construction completion of 19,500 homes and is on track to deliver about 20,000 homes every year for the next three years."

news.title: Mohali development body releases revised plan of 'affordable' colony
news.para: Director of town and country planning, Punjab had released the layout plan of affordable residential colony situated at Chando Gobindgarh village in Kharar tehsil.

news.title: Centre's air quality panel lifts curbs imposed in NCR under GRAP stage 3
news.para: ​The Sub-Committee for invoking actions under the Graded Response Action Plan (GRAP) held a review meeting in view of a significant improvement in the air quality in Delhi-NCR.

news.title: Sebi issues Rs 6.42-crore demand notice to Sahara group firm, Subrata Roy, others
news.para: The regulator, in its order in June, levied a fine totalling Rs 6 crore on five entities -- Sahara India Real Estate Corporation, Subrata Roy, Ashok Roy Choudhary, Ravi Shanker Dubey and Vandana Bharrgava -- for violating regulatory norms in the issuance of OFCDs.

news.title: Greater Noida authority launches group housing scheme on 11 plots
news.para: ​Allotment is being done through e-auction. It is estimated that 10,000 flats will be built on these plots, an official said.

news.title: Issued NBWs against 18 builders this year but police didn't act: Haryana RERA
news.para: ​Non-bailable warrants have been issued by the court of RERA adjudicating officer (AO) against eighteen builders in as many as 86 contempt cases at different times, filed by 86 different complainants, RERA said in an official statement.

news.title: ED provisionally attaches properties of Sobha worth Rs 201.60 crore under PMLA
news.para: Enforcement directorate has provisionally attached certain lands in Kerala valued at Rs. 201.60 crore. The case relates to an inquiry regarding selling plots meant for "no profit no loss" category at exorbitant market prices in the Sobha International City, Gurugram.

news.title: Court directs Delhi police to lodge FIRs against ISH Realtors for duping investors
news.para: The judge directed police to lodge two FIRs against builder firm - ISH Realtors Pvt. Ltd. and it's directors for allegedly committing the offences of criminal conspiracy, criminal breach of trust, fraud, cheating and criminal Intimidation.

news.title: Sebi to auction properties of four companies on January 10
news.para: Of these properties, 16 belongs to Infinity Realcon, five relates to Sumangal Industries and two each to GSHP Realtech and Infocare Infra. These properties include land parcels, plots, single storied buildings and a flat located in West Bengal.

news.title: Macrotech Developers plans $450 million share sale: Sources
news.para: The company has appointed investment banks Jefferies and Kotak to manage the deal, said the sources with direct knowledge of the matter, declining to be identified as a deal is likely to be launched in stock markets this week.

news.title: Four years after making UID numbers must, Ludhiana civic body starts tallying figures
news.para: The survey comes after it was found in a recent check that a few UID numbers did not match property records of the civic body. Now, teams are tallying MC property numbers with UID numbers. At places where UID numbers are not in sequence, they will be changed.

news.title: North Chandigarh leads defaulter list in paying property tax
news.para: Biggest property tax defaulters are residing in the northern part of the city, according to the municipal corporation (MC).The civic body has sent around 2,300 notices in a majority of sectors comprising both the city’s north and south to recover over Rs 4.

news.title: Ludhiana: Pay property tax by December 31 or face fine
news.para: A 10% penalty will be charged on the tax amount from January 1, 2023, till March 31, 2023. From April, the residents will have to pay 20% penalty and 18% per annum interest on the delayed payment.

news.title: Noida: Panel to probe 'irregularities' in plot allotment letters
news.para: YEIDA CEO Arun Vir Singh said, “We have decided to get all the allotment letters issued under the built-up house scheme of 2013. The five-member committee, under the chairmanship of additional CEO Monica Rani, have been given 15 days to conduct the probe and submit a report.”
